Recent experimental papers on quantum cryptography include:
P. D. Townsend, "Secure key distribution system based on quantum 
cryptography," Electronics Letters 30, pg. 809 (1994);
A. Muller et al., "Experimental Demonstration of Quantum Cryptography 
using polarized photons in optical fibre over more than 1 km," 
Europhysics Letters 23, pg. 383 (1993);
J. D. Franson and H. Ilves, "Quantum cryptography using optical fibers," 
Applied Optics 33, pg. 2949 (1994);

A recent theory paper is:
A. Ekert et al., "Eavesdropping on quantum cryptographical systems," 
Physical Review A50, 1047 (1994).

Richard Hughes,
Physics Division,
Los Alamos National Laboratory.
